<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sentinel - if ya unfamilar with this spell then basically its a good spell to use to annoy lots of people quickly.  Functionally it is of no use, its purpose is to tell you if a critter approaches you, but it spams everyone so much it just annoys.  Gonna have fun casting it 4 times around a raid party and watching the whines :><P>Celestial remedy - 65 hps a tick for 4 ticks for 190 mana.  Its at level 19 where the biggest heal you get (other than daring) is a single target 90 point heal with an efficency of 1.5 hp to 1 mana ratio.  This spell has an efficency rating of 1.368 to 1.  Therefore its worse than an instant heal, although at this level it is probably about as quick at healing.  If it is to be of benifit it really needs its mana reducing to 130 so that it is a 2:1 ratio.  Putting it on line with the level 24 greater heal (but over time).  Even so the level 44 celestial healing is about 3.35:1 ratio in comparison to the closest non CH heal of Superior heal being 2.4.  Therefore it being approximately 50% better than a lower level heal is not unbalancing.  making celestial heal to be 50% more efficent than healing would put the mana cost at around 115 for a 260 hp heal.  None the less it needs work.<P>Sermon of the righteous - not tested but its an undead dot, confirmed by trying to cast on a live mob.<P>Sacred word - tried this a bit, mainly cos I had it memed instead of stun command.  The damage component means you have to think much more about using it.  It does seem to have low resist on blue mobs.<P>Armour of faithful - nice solid hp/ac upgrade with a massive duration upgrade.  Its a stepping stone to the one you want, unfortunately all level 50+ spells are mob drops, but initial impressions suggest spells are dropping at an acceptable rate.<P>Overall I must say the store bought spells are a little uninspiring.  As a level 60 cleric it was the 50+ spells that were of most interest to me, but it seem that getting instant spells is against verants principal.<P>Unfortunately the only interesting cleric spells look like blessing of risen, group aegolism and marzin, of which only one truely gives us something new (IE mana regen).<P>none of the classes look to get anything entirely exciting with the store bought spells, except perhaps wizzies with their familar (will have to check out what those are like).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerricoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I gotta say the only spell I am really hanging out for is group aego.<P>2000 mana and 4 periodts.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerricoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I gotta say the only spell I am really hanging out for is group aego.<P>2000 mana and 4 periodts.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Jerricoe Seer<BR>High Priest<BR><A HREF="http://www.redskyeq.com" TARGET=_blank>Red Sky</A> - Bertoxxulous</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Where are these bought?  Can you tell me specifics?<P>/hugs<BR>Torriana Shaddowfists<BR>Cleric<P>Shelsea<BR>Druid<P>Brell Serillis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">No idea Shelsea sorry, I aint got luclin yet so I had to get em from people who had.  Sorry.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kegwell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Found Blessing of Aegolism last nite  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lynet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">They are sold in Shadow Haven, the city that is right off the Nexus.  There are trainers and spell salesmen for all classes in that city.  The cleric spells are, erm, on the east side of the city in a big building.  Eqatlas has a map that is useful.<P>For all classes it looks like most of the sub-50 spells are lite versions of some of the level 50 spells.  They are not useful to folks who are already 50+, but will be very nice to have for the lower level folks.  That said, the mana/heal ration on the heal over time does seem underpowered even for its level.<P>The 52 and 54 spells were dropping like candy in the fungus caves last night.  They might be tweaking the drop rate soon, since 2 spells from a single level 45 critter was very generous indeed.<P>The combination that the high priests should be eying is group aegolism and the top-level skill that makes your group spells into aoe spells.  You should be able to give aegolism to an entire RAID for 4 peridots and most of a tank of mana.<P>Lynet Beaumains, The Damosel Savage</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pastor Skellbane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur I for one would have loved the "mini Cel heal" and undead Dot at those levels. Of course you are not going to find them useful, as you are 60th level. They are designed for lower level people.<P>In your number crunching analysis of Cel Remedy, you forgot to factor in 3 things :-<P>1) Aggro. Heal over time spells generate very little aggro.<P>2) Medding. While it is doing its business you can meditate and get mback the mana.<P>3) Ease of use. Chuck it on a bit earlier than the instant heal, sit back and enjoy.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I like Sacred Word  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">aye stun command and sacred word are quiet good together, sacred word takes a bit longer to cast, but it has a substancially shorter recyle time than stun command.<P>pastor, If you can get back one tick of mana when someone else is pure healing, i would be very surprised.  And at level 19 we are talking a max of what 10 mana?<P>The fact is, the amount it heals is good at that level, but the mana expenditure is prohitive.<P>Also agro is very very small until you reach greater heal.  I honestly can not remember being hit much before getting that spell.  Greater heal is a substancial jump in power between what the tanks are dishing out and what you can heal.<P>A spell that heals over time, should not be less efficent than a direct heal, its just silly.  If Celheal cost 300 mana to cast it would get substancially less use than it does today.<P>Imagine this, if instead of costing 300 mana and healing 1200 hps, CE instead healed 900 hps for 350 mana, would it be anywhere near as good a spell?<P>No, because divine light equally efficent and can be cast instantly.  The agro issue might be ok, but what happens if CE instead cost 400 mana instead of 350?<P>I did compare the spells to the spells we get at the time.  And Celestial remedy whilst healing alot for the level you get it, does it at substancial mana cost.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spells are sold in Katta too.<P>------------------<BR>Splaktar/Gurgel/Samas</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was a bit disappointed that even with partical effect's on full Sanctuary didn't give the light show of Sentinel.<P>If you've ever seen a enchanter playing with sentinal and G-flux, you'd know it was atleast good for a lark.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thotam</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Could only afford to get the first 2 ones, the HoT spell at 19 seems nice enough, although i can see how it is useless for a higher level  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Anyone else reacted on the prices, i bought a druid protection of steel spell that costed 18pp, then i got my wizards lvl 20 DD that one was 31pp  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"> also my necro lvl 20 was 21pp the lvl 49 was 3pp, really wierd.<P><P>------------------<BR>/Thotam lvl 10 human cleric Antonius Bayle</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kinkekk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Why does everyone not like the new spell Celestial Healing?  I think it was a great idea to make that spell.  I personally think it will be very usful for a lvl 19.  It seems to me that only the higher level cleric don't like it.  They need to stop complaining just because it wasn't around when they were lvl 19 so they have no use for it when me a 17 cleric will enjoy having it greatly.  It saves me from waisting mana on the direct heals that only heal about a bub of life on the normal warrior at that lvl.  I can see why they do not like it but come on quit complaining and enjoy that they even took the time to make the dern spell.  I am just waiting til 19 when i can use it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FA